\title{Skill Creator}

\taxon{skill}

\meta{description}{Guide for creating effective skills. Use when users want to create a}

\subtree{
\title{Skill Creator}
\p{Skills are modular packages that extend Claude's capabilities by providing specialized knowledge, workflows, and tools.}

\subtree{
\title{Core Principles}
\subtree{
\title{Concise is Key}
\p{The context window is a shared resource. Only add context Claude doesn't already have. Challenge each piece: "Does Claude really need this?"}
}

\subtree{
\title{Anatomy of a Skill}
\pre{\startverb
skill-name/
├── SKILL.md (required)
│   ├── YAML frontmatter (name, description)
│   └── Markdown instructions
└── Bundled Resources (optional)
    ├── scripts/      - Executable code
    ├── references/   - Documentation
    └── assets/       - Templates, images
\stopverb}
}

\subtree{
\title{SKILL.md Format}
\pre{\startverb
---
name: my-skill-name
description: A clear description of what this skill does and when to use it
---

# My Skill Name

[Instructions for Claude when this skill is active]

## Examples
- Example usage 1
- Example usage 2

## Guidelines
- Guideline 1
- Guideline 2
\stopverb}
}
}

\subtree{
\title{Skill Creation Process}
\subtree{
\title{Step 1: Understand with Examples}
\p{Gather concrete examples of how the skill will be used. Ask:}

\ul{
\li{"What functionality should this skill support?"}
\li{"What would a user say that should trigger this skill?"}
}
}

\subtree{
\title{Step 2: Plan Reusable Contents}
\p{Analyze examples to identify:}

\ul{
\li{\strong{Scripts}: Code that gets rewritten repeatedly}
\li{\strong{References}: Documentation Claude needs to reference}
\li{\strong{Assets}: Templates, images for output}
}
}

\subtree{
\title{Step 3: Initialize}
\p{Create the skill directory structure with SKILL.md and resource folders.}
}

\subtree{
\title{Step 4: Implement}
\ul{
\li{Start with reusable resources (scripts, references, assets)}
\li{Write clear SKILL.md with proper frontmatter}
\li{Test scripts by actually running them}
}
}

\subtree{
\title{Step 5: Iterate}
\p{Use the skill on real tasks, notice struggles, improve.}
}
}

\subtree{
\title{Progressive Disclosure}
\p{Keep SKILL.md under 500 lines. Split content:}

\pre{\startverb
# PDF Processing

## Quick start
[code example]

## Advanced features
- **Form filling**: See [FORMS.md](FORMS.md)
- **API reference**: See [REFERENCE.md](REFERENCE.md)
\stopverb}
}

\subtree{
\title{What NOT to Include}
\ul{
\li{README.md}
\li{INSTALLATION_GUIDE.md}
\li{CHANGELOG.md}
\li{User-facing documentation}
}

\p{Skills are for AI agents, not humans.}
}
}